This paper deals with improving the visual quality of low-light images using a data-driven approach and a deep neural network. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a loss function and perceptual metrics further supports the possibility of it belonging to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and enhancement, which could place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
